  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":")"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","function"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"resolve"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"("}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":")"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"}"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":")"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"where-to-deploy"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#where-to-deploy","ariaLabel":"where to deploy permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Where to Deploy?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Implementing the site using Gatsby and the Kentico Cloud source plugin is super easy and fun, but at the end of the day, there are two questions you should ask:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Where should I host the static files?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How can I automatically regenerate the site when there are content or implementation changes?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The first question is clear; you can keep using the same hosting provider and plan you have currently, right? But with the new implementation, all generated pages are just static files. You probably won’t need the same amount of computing power or server memory. In our case, we decided to host the website on GitHub pages, as the git repository is already hosted there, and the price is very tempting (0 USD). It also supports custom domains."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-link"],"href":"/static/2759dae5b20706a8da5a62494fc75bd7/8ea55/illustration-02.png","style":"display: block","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"],"style":"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 786px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-background-image"],"style":"padding-bottom: 66.96428571428571%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-image"],"style":"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;","alt":"Deploying static site","title":"","src":"/static/2759dae5b20706a8da5a62494fc75bd7/75efb/illustration-02.png","srcSet":["/static/2759dae5b20706a8da5a62494fc75bd7/bea6c/illustration-02.png 197w","/static/2759dae5b20706a8da5a62494fc75bd7/9f6c6/illustration-02.png 393w","/static/2759dae5b20706a8da5a62494fc75bd7/75efb/illustration-02.png 786w","/static/2759dae5b20706a8da5a62494fc75bd7/43bd5/illustration-02.png 1179w","/static/2759dae5b20706a8da5a62494fc75bd7/6a30e/illustration-02.png 1572w","/static/2759dae5b20706a8da5a62494fc75bd7/8ea55/illustration-02.png 2240w"],"sizes":["(max-width:","786px)","100vw,","786px"]},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The answer to the second question is a bit more complicated. A static site needs to be regenerated every time the content or the site’s source code is changed. We are using the Travis CI tool for automatic build and deployment to GitHub pages. When there is an implementation change (push to GitHub repository), Travis is invoked automatically. For content changes, we are using "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://bit.ly/2QzOdeS"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Kentico Cloud webhooks"}]},{"type":"text","value":" - this works flawlessly! Whenever an editor publishes a new content item, webhook notification triggers a Travis build. Travis pulls the content from Kentico Cloud, fetches source code from GitHub, and after few moments of magic combines them into a nice set of static files - your static site. The last step of Travis is deployment to GitHub pages."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"build-a-static-site-today"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#build-a-static-site-today","ariaLabel":"build a static site today permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Build a Static Site Today"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You see, a static site does not necessarily mean static content. Our Kentico Advantage website is not yet live as I am still finalizing full-text search functionality (integration with Azure Search). But I could not wait any longer to share my experience with you. If you want to check out a static site already running on Kentico Cloud and Gatsby, take a look at our "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://bit.ly/2EqdlgO"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Developer Community page"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Do you want your website to be blazing fast, secure, and so comfortable to browse through? A static site is a way to go."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, give it a try and take a look at the starter site in GitHub or sign up for a trial account at "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://bit.ly/2QzUALM"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Kentico Cloud"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and let me know what you think."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Season’s greetings and have a “Static” New Year!"}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"excerpt":"I have to admit I have never really been a fan of JavaScript. I know, shame on me! When I was finishing my studies, I was all about .NET as…","timeToRead":7,"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2018-12-19-kentico-cloud-and-gatsby-take-you-beyond-static-websites/","publishedAt":null},"frontmatter":{"title":"Kentico Cloud & Gatsby Take You Beyond Static Websites","excerpt":null,"date":"January 7th 2019","rawDate":"2019-01-07T00:00:00.000Z","canonicalLink":null,"tags":["react","kentico cloud","graphql"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/32b858bf6fb72b3576f5e7955afd73f0/f1667/teaser.png"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.4,"src":"/static/32b858bf6fb72b3576f5e7955afd73f0/fb26f/teaser.png","srcSet":"/static/32b858bf6fb72b3576f5e7955afd73f0/49912/teaser.png 197w,\n/static/32b858bf6fb72b3576f5e7955afd73f0/0d20f/teaser.png 393w,\n/static/32b858bf6fb72b3576f5e7955afd73f0/fb26f/teaser.png 786w,\n/static/32b858bf6fb72b3576f5e7955afd73f0/71958/teaser.png 1179w,\n/static/32b858bf6fb72b3576f5e7955afd73f0/ac5c2/teaser.png 1572w,\n/static/32b858bf6fb72b3576f5e7955afd73f0/afb0c/teaser.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px"}}},"imageAuthor":null,"imageAuthorLink":null,"imageTitle":"Kentico Cloud and Gatsby","showImageInArticle":null,"author":{"id":"Ondrej Polesny","bio":"Full-stack developer, speaker and trainer with passion for anything new and intriguing. Opensource contributor. Dev evangelist @ Kentico Cloud.","twitter":"@ondrabus","a